'''''Canarium hirsutum''''' is a tree in the family [[Burseraceae]]. The [[specific name (botany)|specific epithet]] ''{{lang|la|[[:wikt:hirsutus|hirsutum]]}}'' is from the [[Latin]] meaning "bristly", referring to the rough hairs of the fruit.<ref name=TFSS/>

==Description==
''Canarium hirsutum'' grows up to {{convert|25|m|-1}} tall with a trunk diameter of up to {{convert|60|cm|0}}. The fruits are oblong to [[:wikt:ovoid|ovoid]] and measure up to {{convert|3.5|cm|in|0|abbr=on}} long.<ref name=TFSS/>

==Distribution and habitat==
''Canarium hirsutum'' grows widely in [[Malesia]] and is also found in the [[Caroline Islands]] and [[Solomon Islands]].<ref name=TFSS/><ref name=COL/> Its habitat is mixed [[dipterocarp]] forest from sea-level to {{convert|1800|m|-3}} altitude.<ref name=TFSS/>

